 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO Osun State Governor, Adegboyega Oyetola, on Thursday announced the upgrade of the State College of Education, Ilesa, to a full-fledged university. The governor said the decision was arrived after painstaking and careful examination of the request made by prominent sons and daughters of Ijesaland to that effect. Oyetola said, “Let me say that, having looked into and examined carefully the request made by prominent sons and daughters of Ijesa Land, and the Owa, our highly-revered Royal Father, His Imperial Majesty, Owa Obokun Adimula of Ijesaland, Oba (Dr.) Gabriel Aromolaran, Government has decided to upgrade the Osun College of Education, Ilesa, to a full-fledged University. “We have also engaged one of the nation’s best corporate Consultants, KPMG, to work out the sustainability plan of the upgrade.” 